 Educational Background



BA in History & Psychology 


Macalester College

                  Founded in 1874, Macalester College has had an intense focus on educating students in an international tradition. It inspires ambitious, committed and talented young people who have the potential to change the world and prepares them to do just that.

Students come to campus to learn, engage, explore, invent, have fun, make friends, devise, design, discover, speak out, and gain the experience, skills and knowledge needed to fulfill their dreams and their greatest ambitions.                





 Career History



Global Head, Consumer & Brand Marketing

                                    2012 - 2017                


Facebook, Inc.


                  Facebook, Inc. engages in the development of useful and engaging products that enable people to connect and share through mobile devices, personal computers, and other surfaces. It enables people to discover and learn events around the world, enable people to share opinions, ideas, photos and videos, and other activities with audiences ranging from closest friends to the public at large. Its products includes Facebook, Instagram, Messenger, WhatsApp, and Oculus. The company was founded by Mark Elliot Zuckerberg, Dustin Moskovitz, Chris R. Hughes, Andrew McCollum and Eduardo P. Saverin on February 4, 2004 and is headquartered in Menlo Park, CA.                




Senior Vice President & Global Chief Marketing Officer

                                    2011 - 2012                


Levi Strauss & Co.


                  Levi Strauss & Co. manufactures and markets jeans and casual apparel. It designs, markets and sells jeans, casual, tops, shorts and skirts and footwear. The company was founded by Levi Strauss in 1873 and is headquartered in San Francisco, CA.                




Head of the Worldwide Marketing & Communications Strategies

                                    2007 - 2011                


Apple, Inc.


                  Apple, Inc. engages in the design, manufacture, and marketing of mobile communication, media devices, personal computers, and portable digital music players. It operates through the following geographical segments: Americas, Europe, Greater China, Japan, and Rest of Asia Pacific. The Americas segment includes both North and South America. The Europe segment consists of European countries, as well as India, the Middle East, and Africa. The Greater China segment comprises of China, Hong Kong, and Taiwan. The Rest of Asia Pacific segment includes Australia and Asian countries not included in the reportable operating segments of the company. The company was founded by Steven Paul Jobs, Ronald Gerald Wayne, and Stephen G. Wozniak on April 1, 1976 and is headquartered in Cupertino, CA.                




Account Director

